\f1\b\fs27 \cf2 \cb5 The Real Problem With OSS Contributor Matchmaker (And It's Fixable)\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf2 \cb5 You're right that it's more marketable. But the judge vulnerability I flagged is real and needs addressing directly.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 \cb5 The problem stated plainly:
\f2\b0 \'a0If you query GitHub issues, GitHub stars, and GitHub commits \'97 that's one API. Coral's whole value proposition is cross-source JOINs. A judge could say "you could do this with three GitHub API calls and a for loop."\cb1 \

\f1\b \cb5 But here's how you fix it completely:
\f2\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb5 Add one external source that makes the JOIN genuinely cross-system. The best candidate:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 \cb5 HackerNews "Who's Hiring" feed + GitHub
\f2\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb5 The insight becomes:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\i \cf6 \cb5 \strokec6 "This repo is actively maintained, has 12 good first issues matching your TypeScript skills, AND the company behind it is currently hiring for the exact role you want. Contributing here is also a job application."
\f2\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb5 \strokec2 That's GitHub + HackerNews in one SQL JOIN. HackerNews has a public API, no auth, and no existing Coral source spec \'97 meaning it's\'a0
\f1\b another clean bounty candidate.
\f2\b0 \cb1 \
\cb5 Or alternatively:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 \cb5 GitHub + Dev.to/Hashnode articles about the repo
\f2\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\i \cf6 \cb5 \strokec6 "This repo has 8 good first issues in React. There are 4 recent blog posts explaining its architecture, meaning onboarding is easier than average. Start here."
\f2\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb5 \strokec2 Either addition makes the cross-source JOIN genuine and irreplaceable.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

