\f1\b\fs27 \cf2 \cb5 The Problem It Solves\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf2 \cb5 Every software project \'97 whether it's a big company's app or a student's side project \'97 is built like a house of cards.\cb1 \
\cb5 You don't build everything yourself. You use other people's pre-built pieces. In the coding world these are called "dependencies" \'97 basically ingredients you borrow from other developers to build your project faster.\cb1 \
\cb5 For example if you're building a website you might use:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf2 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Someone else's login system\cb1 \
\ls4\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Someone else's payment processor\cb1 \
\ls4\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Someone else's date formatter\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb5 Your project depends on all of these working correctly and safely. Hence the name \'97 dependencies.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs27 \cf2 \cb5 Here's The Scary Part\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf2 \cb5 Those borrowed pieces are maintained by other developers. Real humans. Who sometimes:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf2 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Abandon their project
\f2\b0 \'a0\'97 stop updating it, stop fixing bugs, disappear entirely\cb1 \
\ls5\ilvl0
\f1\b \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Get hacked
\f2\b0 \'a0\'97 a bad actor sneaks malicious code into a popular library and suddenly millions of apps using it are compromised\cb1 \
\ls5\ilvl0
\f1\b \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Stop fixing security holes
\f2\b0 \'a0\'97 known vulnerabilities sit unpatched for months or years\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb5 And here's what makes this genuinely terrifying:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 \cb5 The average project has hundreds of these borrowed pieces. Most developers have no idea what state they're in.
\f2\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs27 \cf2 \cb5 A Real Story That Explains Why This Matters\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf2 \cb5 In 2024 a single developer maintained a tiny obscure library called\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf11 \cb12 \strokec11 xz-utils
\f2\fs24 \cf2 \cb5 \strokec2 \'a0that was used inside millions of servers worldwide. A bad actor spent\'a0
\f4\i two years
\f2\i0 \'a0slowly gaining the developer's trust, then snuck in malicious code that could have let them break into any server running it.\cb1 \
\cb5 It was discovered by accident \'97 one developer noticed his SSH login was 500 milliseconds slower than usual and went digging.\cb1 \
\cb5 That's how close it came. One person's curiosity saved millions of servers.\cb1 \
\cb5 The uncomfortable truth:\'a0
\f1\b your side project probably has 5-10 dependencies right now where something similar could happen and you'd have no idea.
\f2\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

